Sample procedure for downloading and running bigdeal under MacOS

1. Download the files (in ~/Downloads)
2. Open a terminal windox and go to wherever you put them. In my case cd ~/Downloads
3. Make them executable: chmod +x bigdeal (and bigdealx)   (Should already be done, just in case)
4. Run it: ./bigdeal
5. You get a popup that tells you that this is not allowed. Click Done
6. Go to "privacy and security" in the system settings. Scroll down to where it says "bigdeal was blocked to protect your mac". Click "allow anyway".
7. Run it again: ./bigdeal
8. You'll be prompted for your password.
9. And then it finally runs.

This is a 1 time exercise, the next time your mac will remember that this is a valid program and just run it.
